main event: Two glowing objects were observed stationary in Trenton, New Jersey on January 7, 1957.
interesting points: The objects' size was compared to that of the moon,The observation lasted for six minutes,There were noted glowing lights on the objects,The sighting was classified as probably caused by an air,Visibility during the observation was reported as good.
witness description: John Booine, age 39, Assistant Commander for Air Cadet Training.
